questlog (1.0.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Project renamed from find-my-session to questlog; command is now questlog.
  * Session viewer is a persistent, full-height pane beside the list from
    launch, showing a placeholder until a session is opened; single-click
    opens a session (was double-click).
  * Match navigation moved into the viewer; match index shown as a floating
    overlay beside the search box.
  * Search terms matched literally (not as regex) in both highlighters.
  * Search matches the whole session, not just the same line.
  * Toolbar (search and criteria controls) scoped to the list column.
  * Assistant blockquotes rendered as collapsible copy boxes in the viewer.
  * Per-session token cost shown as a column in the session list.
  * Session slug shown; right-click menu includes a Rename action.
  * Show-all banner appears when a directory chip was auto-applied.
  * Directory chip seeded from the working directory at launch.
  * Fix: session list was empty when auto-applied directory chip was the
    only active filter.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Fri, 29 May 2026 17:33:30 +0200

